1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO EXEMPT NATURAL HAIR CARE SERVICES, BLOW-DRY STYLING, AND
3 MAKEUP ARTISTRY FROM LICENSING REQUIREMENTS UNDER THE NORTH
4 CAROLINA BOARD OF COSMETIC ART EXAMINERS; TO CONVERT THE
5 MANDATORY NATURAL HAIR CARE SPECIALIST LICENSE TO A VOLUNTARY
6 CERTIFICATE; AND TO EXPAND AUTHORIZED SETTINGS FOR CERTAIN
7 COSMETIC ART SERVICES.
8 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
9
10 PART I. EXEMPTIONS FROM COSMETIC ART LICENSING REQUIREMENTS AND
11 CONVERSION TO VOLUNTARY CERTIFICATION FOR NATURAL HAIR CARE
12 SPECIALISTS
13 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 88B-2 reads as rewritten:
14 "§ 88B-2. Definitions.
15 The following definitions apply in this Chapter:
16 (1) Apprentice. – A person who is not a manager or operator and who is engaged
17 in learning the practice of cosmetic art under the direction and supervision of
18 a cosmetologist.
19 (1a) Blow-dry styling. – The act of shampooing, conditioning, drying, arranging,
20 curling, straightening, or styling hair using only mechanical devices, hair
21 sprays, and topical agents, such as balms, oils, serums, and providing no other
22 services requiring a license under this Chapter. This term includes the use and
23 styling of wigs, hair pieces, and extensions. This term does not include the use
24 of chemicals to alter the structure of the hair and haircutting.
25 (2) Board. – The North Carolina Board of Cosmetic Art Examiners.
26 (3) Booth. – A workstation located within a licensed cosmetic art shop that is
27 operated primarily by one individual in performing cosmetic art services for
28 consumers.
29 (4) Booth renter. – A person who rents a booth in a cosmetic art shop.
30 (4a) Certified natural hair care specialist. – An individual certified by the Board to
31 practice only the part of cosmetic art that constitutes natural hair care, as
32 defined in this section. Certification shall not be required by the Board to
33 practice natural hair care, but an individual who meets the credentials for the
34 certificate may apply to the Board for certification.
35 (5) Cosmetic art. – All or any part or combination of cosmetology, esthetics,
36 natural hair care, or manicuring, including the systematic manipulation with
