7 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 88B-10.1 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 88B-10.1. Qualifications for licensing certifying natural hair care specialists.
9 The Board shall issue a license certificate to practice as a certified natural hair care specialist
10 to any individual who meets all of the following requirements:
11 (1) Successful completion of at least 300 hours of a natural hair care curriculum
12 in an approved cosmetic art school.
13 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
14 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
15 A certificate shall not be required to practice as a natural hair care specialist but shall be
16 required for an individual to hold himself or herself out as or advertise as a certified natural hair
17 care specialist."
