24 SECTION 1.(f) G.S. 88B-14 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 88B-14. Licensing of cosmetic art shops.
26 (a) The Board shall issue a license to operate a cosmetic art shop to any applicant who
27 submits a properly completed application, on a form approved by the Board, pays the required
28 fee, and is determined, after inspection, to be in compliance with the provisions of this Chapter
29 and the Board's rules.
30 (b) The applicant shall list all licensees and all certified natural hair care specialists who
31 practice cosmetic art in the shop and shall identify each as an employee or a booth renter.
32 (c) A cosmetic art shop shall be allowed to operate for a period of 30 days while the
33 Board inspects and determines the shop's compliance with this Chapter and the Board's rules. If
34 the Board is unable to complete the inspection within 30 days, the shop will be authorized to
35 operate until such an inspection can be completed.
36 (d) A license to operate a cosmetic art shop shall not be transferable from one location to
37 another or from one owner to another.
38 (e) A license to operate a cosmetic art shop shall not be required if the cosmetic art
39 services provided in the shop are exclusively natural hair care, blow-dry styling, or makeup
40 artistry, and the persons providing these services are exempt from licensure pursuant to
41 G.S. 88B-25(6). However, if a shop provides natural hair care performed by a certified natural
42 hair care specialist, the Board may inspect those areas of the shop or booths where certified
43 natural hair care specialists practice, limited solely to ensuring compliance with any sanitary
44 management and physical requirements that may be adopted by the Board pursuant to
45 G.S. 88B-4."
