32 SECTION 1.(i) G.S. 88B-21 reads as rewritten:
33 "§ 88B-21. Renewals; expired licenses; inactive status.
34 (a) Each license to operate a cosmetic art shop shall be renewed on or before the first day
35 of February of each year. As provided in G.S. 88B-20, a late fee shall be charged for licenses
36 renewed after February 1. Any license not renewed by March 1 of each year shall expire. A
37 cosmetic art shop whose license has been expired for one year or less shall have the license
38 reinstated immediately upon payment of the reinstatement fee, the late fee, and all unpaid license
39 fees. The licensee shall submit to the Board, as a part of the renewal process, a list of all licensed
40 cosmetologists who practice cosmetic art in the shop and shall identify each as an employee or a
41 booth renter.
42 (b) Cosmetologist licenses shall be renewed on or before October 1 every three years
43 beginning October 1, 1998. A late fee shall be charged for renewals after that date. Any license
44 not renewed shall expire on October 1 of the year that renewal is required. The Board may
45 develop and implement a plan for staggered license renewal and may prorate license fees to
46 implement such a plan.
47 (c) Apprentice, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, and manicurist licenses licenses,
48 and certified natural hair care specialist certificates shall be renewed annually on or before
49 October 1 of each year. A late fee shall be charged for the renewal of licenses after that date. Any
50 license not renewed shall expire on October 1 of that year.
