12 PART III. TRANSITION, IMPLEMENTATION, AND EFFECTIVE DATE
13 SECTION 3.(a) Transition from Licenses to Certificates. – The following provisions
14 shall govern the transition from natural hair care specialist licenses previously required for
15 practice under Chapter 88B of the General Statutes to certified natural hair care specialist
16 certificates, which are voluntary and not required for practice, under this act:
17 (1) Automatic conversion. – All individuals holding valid natural hair care
18 specialist licenses issued by the North Carolina Board of Cosmetic Art
19 Examiners as of the effective date of this act shall automatically be deemed to
20 hold the equivalent certified natural hair care specialist certificates under
21 Chapter 88B of the General Statutes, as amended by this act, without further
22 examination, application, fees, or additional qualification requirements. These
23 certificates confer the title of "certified natural hair care specialist" but are not
24 required to engage in natural hair care services. Holders of these new
25 certificates may continue to provide natural hair care services to the same
26 extent as they did under the previously held licenses, but possession of the
27 certificate is no longer a condition to practice.
28 (2) Pending applications. – Any application for a natural hair care specialist
29 license submitted to the Board prior to the effective date of this act and still
30 pending on that date shall be processed and granted as an application for a
31 certified natural hair care specialist certificate, unless the application does not
32 meet the requirements for certification under Chapter 88B of the General
33 Statutes, as amended by this act. No resubmission or additional qualifications
34 shall be required solely because of the change in designation from license to
35 certificate under this section. Any certificate issued under this subdivision
36 shall be approved under the same conditions and standards that applied to
37 licensure immediately prior to the effective date of this act.
38 (3) Renewal of certificates. – Upon expiration of a natural hair care specialist
39 license converted into a certificate under subdivision (1) of this section, the
40 Board shall permit individuals to renew their credential under the standards
41 applicable to certified natural hair care specialist certificates in accordance
42 with the renewal provisions of G.S. 88B-21, as amended by this act. Nothing
43 in this subdivision shall be construed to require an individual to renew the
44 certificate in order to continue practicing natural hair care services. Renewal
45 merely maintains the use of the "certified natural hair care specialist"
46 designation.
47 SECTION 3.(b) Rulemaking. – The North Carolina Board of Cosmetic Art
48 Examiners may adopt rules to implement the provisions of this act. The Board shall prominently
49 post on its publicly available website information about the exemption created by Section 1(m)
50 of this act, the requirements for completion of the sanitation course necessary for exempt
Senate Bill 656-First Edition Page 9

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 practitioners under G.S. 88B-25(6), and clear instructions for accessing at least one free
2 Board-approved sanitation course that satisfies these requirements.
3 SECTION 3.(c) Effective Date. – This act becomes effective October 1, 2025.
